cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with obstacle detection and classification using lidar and camera sensing, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of conditional random fields for probabilistic fusion is a machine learning technique, which also makes the paper relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves semantic segmentation, which is a natural language processing technique, making it relevant to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
